# Card Pagination: No Scroll, Consistent Paginator

Cards that contain a list of items exceeding visible space **must paginate** — never scroll. Every card paginator must use PrimeNG's `<p-paginator>` component. No custom pagination controls (e.g. "1 / 2" text with chevron buttons).

## Required pattern

```typescript
// Signals
itemPage = signal(0);
itemsPerPage = 3;
itemFirst = computed(() => this.itemPage() * this.itemsPerPage);
paginatedItems = computed(() =>
  this.allItems.slice(this.itemFirst(), this.itemFirst() + this.itemsPerPage)
);
```

```html
<!-- Render paginated slice -->
@for (item of paginatedItems(); track item.id) { ... }

<!-- Paginator at card bottom -->
<p-paginator
    [rows]="itemsPerPage"
    [totalRecords]="allItems.length"
    [first]="itemFirst()"
    (onPageChange)="itemPage.set($event.page ?? 0)"
    styleClass="border-t border-surface-200 dark:border-surface-700"
/>
```

## Rules

1. **Never scroll inside a card.** If items exceed the visible count, paginate.
2. **Always use `<p-paginator>`** from `primeng/paginator` (`PaginatorModule` in imports).
3. **Never build custom pagination** — no manual "X / Y" counters, no chevron `p-button` pairs, no custom next/prev logic.
4. **`styleClass` border** uses `border-t border-surface-200 dark:border-surface-700` to visually separate the paginator from card content.
5. **Signal pattern** must follow `signal(0)` for page index + `computed` for `first` offset and paginated slice.
6. **Apply consistently** across all feature pages (`apps/`, `pages/`) — if you change the paginator pattern, update every instance.
